Structs/Reason.html#/s:13DataCapturing6R.name: explanation
Structs/Reason.html#/s:13DataCapturing6R.abstract: Explains the reason in human understandable text.

Structs/GpsPosition.html#/s:13DataCaptur.name: lat
Structs/GpsPosition.html#/s:13DataCaptur.abstract: The captured latitude of this GpsPosition in decimal coordinates as a value between -90.0 (south pole) and 90.0 (north pole).

Structs/GpsPosition.html#/s:13DataCaptur.name: lon
Structs/GpsPosition.html#/s:13DataCaptur.abstract: The captured longitude of this GpsPositionin decimal coordinates as a value between -180.0 and 180.0.

Structs/GpsPosition.html#/s:13DataCaptur.name: speed
Structs/GpsPosition.html#/s:13DataCaptur.abstract: The current speed fo the measuring device according to its location sensor in meters per second.

Structs/GpsPosition.html#/s:13DataCaptur.name: accuracy
Structs/GpsPosition.html#/s:13DataCaptur.abstract: The current accuracy of the measuring device in meters.

Structs/Reason.html.name: Reason
Structs/Reason.html.abstract: Provides a reason why the DataCapturingService asks for a certain system permission.

Protocols/DataCapturingListener.html#/s:.name: onGpsFixAcquire()
Protocols/DataCapturingListener.html#/s:.abstract: Called everytime the capturing service received a geo location fix and thus is able to track its position.

Protocols/DataCapturingListener.html#/s:.name: onGpsFixLost()
Protocols/DataCapturingListener.html#/s:.abstract: Called everytime the capturing service loses its geo location fix.

Protocols/DataCapturingListener.html#/s:.name: onNewGpsPositionAcquired(position:)
Protocols/DataCapturingListener.html#/s:.abstract: This method is called eacht time the DataCapturingServicereceives a new geo location position.

Protocols/DataCapturingListener.html#/s:.name: onLowDiskSpace(allocation:)
Protocols/DataCapturingListener.html#/s:.abstract: This method is called each time the application runs out of space. How much space is used and how much is available may be retrieved from allocation.

Protocols/DataCapturingListener.html#/s:.name: onRequire(permission:for:)
Protocols/DataCapturingListener.html#/s:.abstract: Invoked each time the `DataCapturingService requires some pemission from the iOS system. That way it is possible to show the user some explanation as to why that permission is required.

Protocols/DataCapturingListener.html#/s:.name: onSynchronizationSuccessful()
Protocols/DataCapturingListener.html#/s:.abstract: Invoked if the service has synchronized all pending cached data successfully and delted the local copies.

Protocols/DataCapturingListener.html.name: DataCapturingListener
Protocols/DataCapturingListener.html.abstract: This protocol defines how to listen for data capturing events.

Classes/Measurement.html#/s:13DataCaptur.name: id
Classes/Measurement.html#/s:13DataCaptur.abstract: The system wide unique identifier of this measurement. Usually this value is generated by a data store (i.e. database).

Classes/DiskConsumption.html#/s:13DataCa.name: consumedBytes
Classes/DiskConsumption.html#/s:13DataCa.abstract: The amount of bytes currently used by the DataCapturingService.

Classes/DiskConsumption.html#/s:13DataCa.name: availableBytes
Classes/DiskConsumption.html#/s:13DataCa.abstract: The amount of bytes still available for the DataCapturingService.

Classes/DiskConsumption.html.name: DiskConsumption
Classes/DiskConsumption.html.abstract: Objects of this class represent the current disk (or rather SD card) space used and available.

Classes/Measurement.html.name: Measurement
Classes/Measurement.html.abstract: An object of this class represents a single measurement captured by the DataCapturingService.
